==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* '''[[gungho]]'''
* '''[[gung-ho]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]:
**[[RP]]: /ɡʌŋ-ˈhəʊ/
**[[GenAm]]: /ɡʌŋ-ˈhoŭ/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]:
**[[RP]]: /gVN-'h@U/
**[[GenAm]]: /gVN-'hou(/

===Etymology===
From a World War II [[catachresis]] of Mandarin Chinese ''gōnghé'' ([[工]] ''gōng'', work + [[合]] ''hé'', together), itself an acronym for ''gōngyè hézuòshè'' ([[工業]][[合作社]], [[工业]][[合作社]] Chinese Industrial Cooperative Society).

===Adjective===
'''gung ho'''

# (informal, disapproving) very [[enthusiasm|enthusiastic]] or [[energy|energetic]]
#:''No matter how gung ho you are when you start, you will tire as you become mired in details.''

